Package: pafr
Title: Read, Manipulate and Visualize 'Pairwise mApping Format' Data
Version: 0.0.2
Authors@R: c( person("David", "Winter", email =
        "david.winter@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment =
        c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6165-0029")), person("Kate", "Lee", email
        = "kate.d.lee@gmail.com", role = c("ctb"), comment = c(ORCID =
        "0000-0002-0886-3746")), person("Murray", "Cox", email =
        "m.p.cox@massey.ac.nz", role = c("ctb"), comment = c(ORCID =
        "0000-0003-1936-0236")))
Description: Provides functions to read, process and visualize pairwise
        sequence alignments in the 'PAF' format used by 'minimap2' and
        other whole-genome aligners. 'minimap2' is described by Li H.
        (2018) <doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/bty191>.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.4), ggplot2,
